==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epitasis
<hw>E*pit"a*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ a stretching, fr. <?/ to stretch upon or over; <grk>'epi`</grk> upon
+ <?/ to stretch.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That part which embraces the
main action of a play, poem, and the like, and leads on to the
catastrophe; -- opposed to <contr>protasis</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The period of violence in a fever
or disease; paroxysm.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epithalamic</ent>⟦br⟧
